==Corporate==

===Membership base and sponsorship===
Crowds and memberships for the Brisbane Lions grew dramatically during the four seasons in which they made the AFL Grand Final. Since then, with the team being less successful, attendances have declined, but have remained stable over the past three seasons. In 2009 the Lions found it so difficult to sell corporate boxes that they resorted to doing so on a game-by-game basis.<ref>[http://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/afl/lions-hit-by-fall-in-sales/story-e6frf9jf-1225697726606 Lions hit by fall in corporate box sales] heraldson.com.au. Retrieved 27 September 2009.</ref> 2011 saw the Brisbane Lions suffer their worst ever drop in support, as memberships decreased by 28%. Consequently, the Brisbane Lions have the third lowest membership in the AFL.<ref>{{Cite news| last=Macgugan| first=Mark| title=
Clubs post membership record| publisher=[[Australian Football League|AFL]]| date=19 July 2011| url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/newsarticle/tabid/208/newsid/118901/default.aspx| accessdate=28 July 2011}}</ref>

