===Financial performance===
In 2008 the Brisbane Lions recorded a loss of $2,200,200.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/lions-cop-22-million-wound/story-fna7dq6e-1111118267900|first=Andrew|last=Hamilton | title=Brisbane Lions announce overall loss of $2.2 million | date=9 December 2008|accessdate=25 June 2012}}</ref> CEO Michael Bowers was reported to be "buoyed" when 2009 membership exceeded its 2008 total by 8 April 2009.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,25321644-19746,00.html?from=public_rss | title=Lions hit by fall in corporate box sales | first=Greg | last=Davis | date=12 April 2009 | work=Sunday Herald Sun}}</ref> In 2009 the Brisbane Lions recorded a further loss of $603,207.<ref>[http://sportal.com.au/afl-news-display/lions-record-big-financial-loss-81769 AFL – News, Footy News – Sportal<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==Club symbols==

===Guernseys===

The three types of guernsey are:

*Home guernsey (worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Maroon and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and maroon. [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on front and [[Conergy]] sponsor on back (home pants worn in home games and away pants worn in away games not played in Victoria).

*Away guernsey (Worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Red and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and red. [[Conergy]] sponsor on front and [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on back (away pants worn).

*Clash guernsey (Worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Maroon, white and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and maroon.  [[Conergy]] sponsor on front and [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on back (away pants worn).
[[File:Lions mascot.jpg|thumb|70px|left|Bernie Gabba Vegas]]

===Mascot===
The Lion's [[Mascot Manor]] representative and club mascot is Bernie "Gabba" Vegas, a caricature of a lion dressed in Brisbane Lions jumper, sunglasses, wide lapels and flares, designed to resemble [[Elvis Presley]].

===Song===
The club's team song, ''The Pride of Brisbane Town'' is based on the Fitzroy club song, and is sung to the music of "[[La Marseillaise]]", the French national anthem:<ref name="ABC_AM_29Oct2009_Eastly">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/am/content/2009/s2727075.htm|title=Brisbane Lions face court action over new logo|last=[[Tony Eastley]]|date=29 October 2009|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=10 April 2010}}</ref>

''We are the pride of Brisbane town,''
''we wear maroon, blue and gold,''
''we will always fight for victory,''
''like Fitzroy and Bears of old,''
''all for one, and one for all,''
''we will answer to the call,''
''go Lions, Brisbane Lions,''
''we'll kick the winning score,''
''you'll hear our mighty roar!''

